Aux:TextAnnotations.Aux:document_text: MEMORANDUM OF AGREEMENT FOR EMPLOYEE SERVICES TENNESSEE BOARD of REGENTS VENDOR PARTY TENNESSEE STATE UNIVERSITY PROCURING PARTY THIS AGREEMENT signifies agreement of the above parties concerning the provisions of employee services. The agreement is as follows: 1. Vendor agrees to furnish the services of its employee William Arnold , Social Security Numt__who will perform the following services for Procuring Party: Teaching PRST 5310: Leadership in Organization - Section R51 3 hour course. 2. Compensation to Vendor Party: Salary: $2,100, plus cost of any applicable staff fringe benefits: $370,65, Maximum liability of Procuring Party not to exceed $2,470. 3. Payment will be made by Procuring Party after completion of service and after receipt of invoice from Vendor Party, mailed to the following address: 330 10th Avenue North Box 139 Nashville, Tennessee 37203-3401 4. The effective date and term of this agreement shall be from August 14, 2008 to December 16, 2008. 5. Coordinator for: Vendor Party Tennessee Board of Regents Tel: (615) 366-4436 Procuring Party Bruce Rogers Tel: (615) 963-7248 6. Either party may terminate this Agreement by giving written notice to the other at least_____days before the effective date of termination. In that event, Vendor shall be entitled to receive just and equitable compensation for any satisfactory work completed as of the termination date. 7. This agreement cannot be assigned or subcontracted without the prior written consent of all parties. 8. During the performance of this Agreement both parties warrant that they will not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, age, religion, creed, color, sex, disability, Veteran status, or national origin. The parties will take affirmative action to ensure that applicants are employed and that employees are treated during employment without regard to their race, age, religion, creed, color, sex, disability, Veteran status, or national origin. Such action shall include, but not be limited to the following: employment, upgrading, demotion, transfer, recruitment or recruitment advertising, layoff or termination, rates of pay or other forms of compensation, and selection available to employees and applicants for employment. DATED THIS 4th DAY OF AUGUST, 2008. PROCURING PARTY By: Melvin N. Johnsen ' Title: ________President________________________ Date: TSU-Purchasing & Business Services (rev. 8/03)
